Finally, in the standard bivariate plot of muzzle proportions (
Fig. 8
), two groups can be recognized. The first includes the specimen from the fossiliferous sites referred to glacial stages (
Appendix 9
), which display a large muzzle in relation to their length. An exception is the cranium of 

Equus ferus antunesi
Cardoso and Eisenmann, 1989

from Fontainhas (
Portugal
